                <note rend="inline" type="source">150.01/802</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Norwegian Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bryn</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-03-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 19, 1924</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note dated February 20, 1924, with respect to certain provisions of the new
                    immigration bill (H. R. 6540) introduced in the House of Representatives on
                    February 1, 1924.</p>
                <p>You may be assured that all questions relating to the appropriate recognition of
                    the treaty provisions to which you refer are having proper consideration.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles E. Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
